Case 1:20-cr-00330-PAE Document 763 Filed 08/10/22 Page 195 of 197 2736 LCHCmax7
1 THE COURT: Start with Ms. Williams. I guess it depends what it is. We'll have some staff here tomorrow for the charging conference, but Ms. Williams will be reachable no matter what over the weekend and she can direct traffic.
2 MS. MOE: Thank you very much, your Honor. Just wanted to work that out in advance.
3 THE COURT: Thank you.
4 MS. STERNHEIM: Judge, at this time, we would reiterate and renew our motion pursuant to Rule 29.
5 THE COURT: With that reservation, we can proceed to the charging conference.
6 Anything else to take up?
7 MS. MOE: Not from the government, your Honor. Thank you.
8 MR. EVERDELL: Not from the defense, your Honor.
9 THE COURT: I thank everyone. I'll see everyone at 9:00. You'll get the charge as soon as I can, but by 6:00.
10 (Adjourned to December 18, 2021 at 9:00 a.m.)
11 * * *
12 SOUTHERN DISTRICT REPORTERS, P.C. (212) 805-0300
13 DOJ-OGR-00014301
